node.text:
HNY / Bonne année!

Thank you for hanging in this neck of the internet woods. Wishing you lots of health, good coffees, time in nature, time in the present, unleashing your creativity, and meeting good people. This year was a challenging one but as Voltaire said, “The hardest decision you make each day is to be in a good mood.”

Have a great year ✌🏻

node.text:
Had a lot of fun making this film for @prada’s new Luna Rossa Ocean as a #PradaPartner… On my exploration of the fragrance I saw the moon set over the Atlantic, drove one of my favorite cars #912, and witnessed the most vivid sunset on earth. Or at least I thought it was.  Hope you enjoy this piece as much as I enjoyed creating it.

2nd camera @platoux
Edit @inmistmediahouse
Sound design @un.studios 

#PradaPartner #PradaLunaRossaOcean @ultabeauty

Let me know what else you’d like to see edited!

Music: Two One, Four - @fyfemusic

node.text:
Chasing success, striving to be the “best” will make you unhappy because those are things that others measure for you. It’s external. 

Fulfillment however is something you can measure, only you. It’s internal. 

And as photographers we tend to put a lot of imaginary barriers that prevent us from being fulfilled in our craft. 

Heading into the new year, I’ve made a new workshop to help you remove those barriers. (Hint: they’re mostly within our heads). 

Goal setting, motivation, systems and routines... I cover it all. 

The workshop is on a limited pre-order. Link in bio :)

node.text: The kind of light that only exists in the winter.. Tonight’s sunset straight out of camera #sooc

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alex Strohl on January 04, 2022 tagging @66north, and @chrisburkard. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Chris thought it would be a good idea to check if we could ride the length of this beach — the most photographed in Iceland. 

After an 85 mile day with heinous headwinds, I was a bit hesitant to do the 6 mile detour but thought to myself: “when’s the next time you’ll be able to try this?”

Well… It turns out you can ride this beach. Some parts we sank to our ankles and others were firm as tarmac. We got some good laughs, these photos, and probably ruined our bike chains in the process. Worth it!

node.text:
HNY / Bonne année!

Thank you for hanging in this neck of the internet woods. Wishing you lots of health, good coffees, time in nature, time in the present, unleashing your creativity, and meeting good people. This year was a challenging one but as Voltaire said, “The hardest decision you make each day is to be in a good mood.”

Have a great year ✌🏻

node.text: Our friends at @on_running hired us for a very special mission: to take a break and appreciate the world around us. So @andreadabene and I went for a  day of walking around Chamonix on the snowiest December they’ve had in a while.. Pure magic

user.full_name: B E N   T I B B E T T S

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alex Strohl in Chamonix, France with @bentibbettsphotography. May be an image of sky and nature.

node.text:
The Aiguille Du Plan a few nights ago during a particularly perfect sunset. Perhaps the most exciting part about this view is that I was able to get to it by simply skiing from the house. I’ve spent the last four sunsets up here in front of the Mont-Blanc Massif and every one is different in its own way… 

Delighted with our backyard courtesy of the @chilldernessescapes #chaletfnet

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alex Strohl on December 12, 2021 tagging @canonusa. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
One of the highlights of 2021 was shooting for @CanonUSA’s new EOS R6 in this very hard to access fire lookout in Montana. We barely slept at night because the wind gusts were so strong we thought the roof was going to fly away. The days were magical in contrast: skiing around, looking for spots to jump off and shooting photos. 

When people ask what would be my desert island camera I always struggle between the EOS R5 and the EOS R6 — the former has all the specs (45MP, 8K video…) but I love how nimble and light the latter is for human powered trips.

node.text:
In partnership with @CanonUSA — Caught a glimpse of the pre-historic times when this herd of wild reindeer crested over the hill… Making this series for @CanonUSA’s RF 100-500mm F4.5-7.1 L IS USM lens & the EOS R5 involved long memorable days of crawling through the early snow in search of these creatures. I’ve been using this lens for two years and the more I use it the more I’m hooked on it — it does 90% of what a RF 600mm F4 L IS USM F4 does for a fraction of the weight, bulk and price. I’m hooked. 
 
I’m still processing the beauty of the encounter — which lasted about 4 minutes — but for now I can safely say that I’ve never been that moved by a wild animal. They came out of nowhere, gracefully looked around, ate some, and disappeared into the ether. 
 
PS. This series couldn’t have been possible without the invaluable help of @jeremievillet who knows these animals inside and out. #canoncreator

node.text:
-26°F / -32°C 

Thankful for all your kind comments and messages about our incoming family member, so nice seeing all these familiar faces and names. 

It was 10 years ago this month that I heard through a college friend about this little photo app called Instagram. I signed up immediately and started taking photos of snow piles at dusk… What a ride it’s been. Thanks for being around 🙂
